, 1993|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|1994\n|''[[Baseball (TV series)|Baseball]]''\n|{{sortname|Kid|Gleason}} / [[Connie Mack]]\n|Voice, Documentary miniseries\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|{{sfn|Molyneaux|1995|p=257}}\n|-\n!scope=row|1998\n|''[[Moby Dick (1998 miniseries)|Moby Dick]]''\n|{{sortname|Father|Mapple|nolink=1}}\n|Television miniseries\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1998-mar-15-tv-29512-story.html|work=Los Angeles Times|title=Stewart\u2019s Visit to Melville|date=March 15, 1998|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|1999\n|''American Prophet: The Story of Joseph Smith''\n|Narrator\n|Documentary\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.deseret.com/2017/9/25/20620213/old-joseph-smith-pbs-documentary-remade-into-new-docudrama-depicting-american-prophet-s-polarizing-l#joseph-smith-writes-a-letter-from-missouris-liberty-jail-in-a-scene-from-the-new-historical-docudrama-joseph-smith-american-prophet|title=Old Joseph Smith PBS documentary remade into new docudrama depicting 'American Prophet's' polarizing life|last=Toone|first=Trent|work=Deseret News|date=September 25, 2017|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Stage==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"| Year(s)\n!scope=\"col\"| Title\n!scope=\"col\"| Role\n!scope=\"col\"|Theatre\n!scope=col class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n!scope=col class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=row|1942\n|''{{sortname|The|Morning Star|nolink=1}}''\n|{{sortname|Cliff|Parrilow|nolink=1}}\n|[[Morosco Theatre]]\n|September 14 \u2013 October 3\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=IBDB>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibdb.com/broadway-cast-staff/gregory-peck-55817|title=Gregory Peck|publisher=Internet Broadway Database|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|1942\u20131943\n|''{{sortname|The|Willow and I|nolink=1}}''\n|{{sortname|Kirkland|Todd|nolink